This paper discusses the optimization of dynamic spectrum access and the utilization of green energy in wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). It also involves the optimization of energy harvesting and management, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the state of the art of energy efficient CR-based wireless access networks, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
